      "id": "FollowupBenignBiopsyResult",
      "title": "Continue routine screening",
      "description": "Benign lesions without atypia or discordance with imaging can return to routine screening.\n\nCertain specific benign histologies may require additional tissue, including mucin-producing lesions, potential phyllodes tumor, papillary lesions, or radial scars. Refer to pathologist for further recommendations.\n\nOther specific histologies may be considered for excisional biopsy and can be referred to a breast surgeon for evaluation. These may include flat epithelial atypia [FEA], papillary and/or sclerosing lesion, and fibroepithelial lesions (fibroadenoma vs benign phyllodes tumor).",
      "definitionCanonical": "http://cancerscreeningcds.github.io/bcsm-cds/ActivityDefinition/BreastCancerScreeningServiceRequest|1.0.0"
    },
    {
